Rating: 0
I love this recipe and have gotten rave reviews for it. However, I've made it into a cheese ball, rather than spread it on the bread. I mix the first four ingredients with a bit of sour cream. I put it into the freezer for 15-20 minutes (till it stiffens up a bit), then roll it in a ball. I rolled it in parsley flakes, crushed walnuts, and a pinch or two of red pepper flakes. It looks festive and tastes great with crackers. Lovely. I haven't tried it yet with basil, but I will. It will be great, I'm sure.

Rating: 4
Super yum and super easy! Don't skimp on the nuts. I think it makes the dish.

Rating: 4
Guests raved at how good it was. I used one jar of sun- dried tomatoes, 5 1/2 oz. container of goat cheese, and fresh basil (no thyme, no walnuts), thinned a little with non-fat sour cream. Yum. Served with cuke slices and radishes with their tops attached. Due to some other reviewer's concern about the appearance, I made sure to add some basil as decoration on the top, and put a colorful hors d'oeuvres knife in the dip so people could spread it if they chose. It looked appetizing next to the colorful cukes and radishes. When I said "last call" before I put it away, the guests quickly dipped into it one more time. I'll save the recipe and gladly make it again.

