Rating: 4
Use sun-dried tomatoes that are not packed in oil. Pour boiling water over the tomatoes and let set about five minutes. Drain, pat dry and chop. I did not add the walnuts nor any of the spices; instead I used peppercorn feta to add a bit of spice. Served it in a ramikin with freshly baked sourdough. Oh, what a fantastic dish! Served it to friends on Christmas eve and they couldn't get enough. In order to make the mixtrue truly creamy and spreadable I used my food processor. If a chef would like a crunchier dip almonds or walnuts could be easily blended into the dip (by hand) before placing in a dish for serving.

